The paper is about named entity recognition and mention detection in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed approach uses a neural network, which involves machine learning techniques and can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the CoNLL 2003 NER task, which is a well-known benchmark dataset for NER, and TAC-KBP2015 and TAC-KBP2016 Tri-lingual Entity Discovery and Linking (EDL) tasks, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing.
